Don't use the wrong tools. pxp and xmlm follow the standard (xmlm up =20
to exceptions documented here [1]). xmlm is as light as xml-light but =20=

is not a toy. If you have been using xml-light this blog post [2] has =20=

thirty lines of code to produce xml-light's representation with xmlm.

